+// compat shim: js-tokens@10 is an ESM-only generator tokenizer whose default
+// export is `function* jsTokens(input)` — a different API from js-tokens@4,
+// whose default export was a single sticky regex plus a `matchToToken(match)`
+// helper. @babel/code-frame@7.29 still does `require('js-tokens')` then
+// `jsTokens.default.exec(text)` + `jsTokens.matchToToken(match)` (the v4 API),
+// so a CommonJS `require` on js-tokens@10 would receive the v10 generator and
+// break. Restore the js-tokens@4 regex API verbatim on the `require` condition;
+// the modern `function*` generator stays on the `import` condition (used by
+// e.g. ast-v8-to-istanbul), untouched.
+
